- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with predicting link decay in social networks and other network structures.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the development of a new approach (DecLiNe) for predicting link decay in networks.
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper focuses on social networks and their analysis.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of machine learning methods for predicting link decay.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the analysis of large-scale datasets of Wikipedia.
